ors.org/data.show.php?di=record&da=encyclopedia&ke=98 Encyclopedia \u2013 \"Hidden Jews\"]. Holocaust Survivors. Retrieved on 22 August 2010.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hnetradz\">[http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showrev.cgi?path=252691081495762 Unveiling the Secret City] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070612051615/http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showrev.cgi?path=252691081495762 |date=12 June 2007 }} H-Net Review: John Radzilowski</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"jcpa.org\">[http://www.jcpa.org/cjc/cjc-schudrich-06.htm The Chief Rabbi's View on Jews and Poland \u2013 Michael Schudrich]. Jcpa.org. Retrieved on 22 August 2010.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"jewishvirtuallibrary.org\">[https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/vjw/Warsaw.html The Virtual Jewish History Tour \u2013 Warsaw]. Jewishvirtuallibrary.org. Retrieved on 22 August 2010.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"lukas\">Richard Lukas ''Forgotten Holocaust'', Hippocrene Books, 2nd revised ed., 2001, {{ISBN|0-7818-0901-0}}.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"opoczno-1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.opoczno.pl/opoczno/_portal/117189707245d9baf044536/Zabytki.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081205110952/http://www.opoczno.pl/opoczno/_portal/117189707245d9baf044536/Zabytki.html|url-status=dead|title=Official portal of the city of Opoczno|archivedate=5 December 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"partners-1\">[http://www.friends-partners.org/partners/beyond-the-pale/index.html Beyond the Pale] Online exposition</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"polish-jewish-heritage.org\">[http://www.polish-jewish-heritage.org/eng/05-01_Polan_Selects_New_Chief_Rabbi.htm The Canadian Foundation of Polish-Jewish Heritage]. Polish-jewish-heritage.org (8 January 2005). Retrieved on 2010-08-22.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"relations\">[https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/vjw/Poland.html The Virtual Jewish History Tour \u2013 Poland]. Jewishvirtuallibrary.org. Retrieved on 22 August 2010.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"response\">[http://www.fathom.com/course/72809602/session3.html Poland's Century: War, Communism and Anti-Semitism] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307025436/http://www.fathom.com/course/72809602/session3.html |date=7 March 2009 }}. Fathom.com. Retrieved on 22 August 2010.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"stroop\">From the [https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/nowarsaw.html Stroop Report] by SS [[Gruppenf\u00fchrer]] J\u00fcrgen Stroop, May 1943.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"LJW\">[http://www1.yadvashem.org.il/about_holocaust/lost_worlds/grodno/grodno_during_ww1.html Lost Jewish Worlds \u2013 Grodno, Yad Vashem] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20090719032015/http://www1.yadvashem.org.il/about_holocaust/lost_worlds/grodno/grodno_during_ww1.html |date=19 July 2009 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ynet\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-3376540,00.html|title=\u05d3\u05e8\u05db\u05d5\u05df \u05e4\u05d5\u05dc\u05e0\u05d9 \u05d1\u05d6\u05db\u05d5\u05ea \u05d4\u05e1\u05d1\u05ea\u05d0 \u05de\u05d5\u05d5\u05e8\u05e9\u05d4|date=16 March 2007|website=ynet}}</ref>\n\n<!--unused ref<ref name=\"zydziwpolsce\">{{cite web |url=http://www.zydziwpolsce.edu.pl/panel23.html |title=\u017bydzi dzisiaj. Tablica 23 |publisher=Fundacja Stefana Batorego |year=2010 |accessdate=23 July 2011 |author=A & K Wo\u017aniak}}</ref>-->\n}}\n\n==References==\n* [[Marek Jan Chodakiewicz]], ''After the Holocaust'', East European Monographs, 2003, {{ISBN|0-88033-511-4}}.\n* [[Marek Jan Chodakiewicz]], ''Between Nazis and Soviets: Occupation Politics in Poland, 1939\u20131947'', [[Lexington Books]], 2004, {{nobreak|{{ISBN|0-7391-0484-5}}}}.\n* [[William W. Hagen]], \"Before the 'Final Solution': Toward a Comparative Analysis of Political Anti-Semitism in Interwar Germany and Poland\", ''[[The Journal of Modern History]]'', Vol. 68, No. 2 (Jun. 1996), 351\u2013381.\n* {{cite book |last = Hundert |first = Gershon David |title = Jews in Poland-Lithuania in the Eighteenth Century: A Genealogy of Modernity |year = 2004 |publisher = [[University of